      "writtenOn": "2026-03-11T16:10:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The watcher fires on every change to any of the four reactive sources. If the query is already cached when the component mounts (e.g., navigating back to Overview after visiting Power), immediate: true will emit overview-power-complete instantly. Then any background refetch (if refetch options are enabled in the future) would cause isFetching to toggle false→true→false, emitting the event again.\n\nThe Overview page presumably uses this event to track loading. Emitting it multiple times may be harmless if the consumer is idempotent, but it\u0027s worth considering a once pattern:\n```\nconst emitted \u003d ref(false);\nwatch(..., () \u003d\u003e {\n  if (settled \u0026\u0026 !emitted.value) {\n    emitted.value \u003d true;\n    eventBus.$emit(\u0027overview-power-complete\u0027);\n  }\n});\n```",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 54,
        "endChar": 0
      },
